      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "013b97fe_5db8b8d9",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/aai/components/aai-traversal/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 44,
      "message": "Hi, while the \"keycloak.your.domain\" may provide an example, the \"localhost\" actually matches with the development config in the \"traversal\" repo as well. One can argue that, it would be easier to maintain automation script to update and replace these config values. This is also the default for the \"aai-resources\" component so no surprise for user. 😊\n\nWith regards to Keycloak's realm and roles settings, there is no expectations whatsoever. It is up to the application's configuration requirement to setup the realm, client-app and access roles.\n\nThanks",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6932,
        "name": "Sam Huang",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sam.huang@yoppworks.com",
        "username": "sam.huang"
      },
      "updated": "2021-04-07 04:48:20.000000000",
